Set Up

Thanks for your interest in learning R. For the CERF R workshop, we will be using RStudio as our interface to R. In order to participate in this workshop you will need to make sure you have R and RStudio installed on your laptop. The instructions below should help you get all the software installed that we will need.

Install R

Install RStudio

Install packages

Exercise 1

Just to make sure everything is working do the following:

  1. Open up RStudio.
  2. Find the Console. This is usually the left part RStudio.
  3. In the Console, find the R Prompt.
  4. Type in (copy and paste from here will also work) the following commands at the R Prompt and hit return.
"dplyr" %in% installed.packages()
"ggplot2" %in% installed.packages()
